備註 Remarks





基本素養 Basic Literacy
□ 厚植人文素養及西洋文學文化涵養
 To cultivate their spirit of humanity and increase their knowledge of western literatures and cultures.
■ 獨立思考、思辨、反省與推己及人
 To think independently, analyze critically, reflect and sympathy
■ 發揮專業、擴展國際視野、跨界學習
 To demonstrate their professionalism, broaden their international perspectives and interdisciplinary studies
 

核心能力 Competence
□ 人文素養與社會關懷能力
 Ability to provide social concern with a spirit of humanity
■ 熟稔各種理論基礎、收集分析文獻資料的能力
 Ability to collect and analyze literature data with various theoretical foundations
■ 完成學術論文及批判性書寫的能力
 Ability to work on academic papers and critical writing
■ 深入閱讀並解析外國文學、語言、文化等作品與論文的能力
 Ability to read and analyze works or academic papers on foreign literatures, languages and cultures
□ 國際視野、跨領域研究及適應能力
 Ability to conduct interdisciplinary studies from international perspectives
■ 獨立思考、團隊合作、創意研究及分析、解決問題的能力
 Abilities to think independently, to perform a teamwork, to conduct creative research and analysis, and to solve problems.
 

課程概述 Course Description
       此課程將提供學生認知語言學的幾個主題，顏色、物品、經濟、廣告等都是可能的課題。學生可自由選擇自己所感興趣的主題來做相關的討論，希望能激發學生們對認知語言學的思考，以及參與做相關認知語言學研究的興趣。
本課程包括以下的主題：
? 認知語言學的相關理論
? 從語言學到各主題的認知語言學
? 顏色、物品
? 經濟、廣告
? 文化思維
The goal of this course is to solidify students’ knowledge about Cognitive Linguistics, such as color, artifacts, economics, commercials. It is hope that students will choose the topic that they are interested in to explore the field of Cognitive Linguistics. 
 
The following topics on Cognitive Linguistics will be presented and the related readings will be given for class discussion. Topics to be covered: (1) Theories of Cognitive Linguistics, (2) From Linguistics to the sub-fields of Cognitive Linguistics, (3) color or artifacts, (4) economics or commercials, and (5) modes of thinking. 
    

課程學習目標 Course Objectives
Solidify students’ knowledge about Cognitive Linguistics.A term paper is required at the end of the semester. Students develop interest in the field of Cognitive Linguistics. 

課程進度 Course Outline


週次 Week進度說明 Progress Description
1Orientation2Cognitive theory of Linguistics3Method of investigation4Artifacts (Assignment:experimental design)5Oral presentation (assignment)6School activity (topic of term paper)7Oral presentation(thesis statement)8Your topics & discussion9Mid term10Naming11Commercial advertisements12Economic issues13Political issues14Research on cognitive linguistics (senior students come over)15Research on cognitive linguistics16Expressions and modes of thinking (draft)17Does it constitute or reflect cultural models (term paper due)18Presentation of students’ term papers 

　以上每週進度教師可依上課情況做適度調整。The schedule may be subject to change.


