專業領域 
語意學、認知語言學、應用德文




 



 Shelley Ching-yu Hsieh is a professor at Department of Foreign Languages and Literature in National Cheng Kung University, Taiwan. She has a PhD in Linguistics from Tübingen University, Germany in 2001. The focus of her research is a cross-cultural comparison of the cognitive semantics and sociolinguistics of Mandarin Chinese and German.




 



